<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Components: &lt;ID (ST)&gt; ^ &lt;check digit (ST)&gt; ^ &lt;code identifying the check digit scheme employed (ID)&gt; ^ &lt; assigning authority (HD)&gt; ^ &lt;identifier type code (IS)&gt; ^ &lt; assigning facility (HD)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">This parameter restricts the set of domains for which identifiers are returned in PID-3. If this is not specified, then identifiers for all known domains shall be returned. It does not restrict the search for the person.</p></td>
